\newcommand{\resultssecondblock}{
\begin{alertblock}{Wifi coverage - Ignoring phase}
\alertblockcolours
\begin{itemize}
\item The strength of the field is calculated in two parts accounting for the \textbf{attenuation in free space} and the \textbf{reduction at the reflections}. 
\item Let $u_r$, $u_t$ be the field strength at the receiver and transmitter relatively. \textbf{The Friis transmission formula} gives the loss resulting from the spread from the antenna:
\begin{equation}
\label{eqn::FriisTransmissFormula}
\frac{|u_r|}{|u_t|}=\sqrt{G_a G_b} \left( \frac{\lambda}{4 \pi r} \right), \hspace{0.1\linewidth}\cite{aragon2008antennas}
\end{equation} 
The antenna has no preferred direction so the gains for the antenna's $G_a$ and $G_b$ are $1$. 

\item Figure \ref{fig::signalcoverage} shows the signal strength for two \textbf{different transmitter locations}.
